    "description": "<p data-block-key=\"ko1gu\"><i>World History, Volume 2: from 1400</i> is designed to meet the scope and sequence of a world history course from 1400 offered at both two-year and four-year institutions. Suitable for both majors and non majors <i>World History, Volume 2: from 1400</i> introduces students to a global perspective of history couched in an engaging narrative. Concepts and assessments help students think critically about the issues they encounter so they can broaden their perspective of global history. A special effort has been made to introduce and juxtapose people’s experiences of history for a rich and nuanced discussion. Primary source material represents the cultures being discussed from a firsthand perspective whenever possible. <i>World History, Volume 2: from 1400</i> also includes the work of diverse and underrepresented scholars to ensure a full range of perspectives.</p><p data-block-key=\"7nfem\"></p><p data-block-key=\"dr0ka\">Print copies of this book will be available for the fall 2023 semester. You can <a href=\"https://www.xanedu.com/openstax-pre-order\">sign up to be notified when print copies are available</a>.<br/></p>",
